It's durability, its playability.<br>
The potential for more expansions, the existing expansions.<br>
The content, and the possibility of improvement.<br>
The competition, and EQ's success in beating it off.<br>
The increasing interest in RPG's, specifcally those Online.<br>
The server population increases.<br>
Customer service, Nerfs, Management decisions.<br>
And finally, the age of EQ, people growing out of it, or growing in to it.<br>
<br>
I think the most important factors when considering said question, is EverQuests playability, which for prety much all of us.. is obviously high. Also, I think the expansion/possibility for more is something to consider. EQ seems a world with endless possilibities. And lastly, I think it's important to focus on competition. There are so many more MMPORPG's coming out now, will they compare?<br>
So, how long do you give EverQuest until it wears out its welcome, collapses, or just fades away? Please, limit the 'im outta here when SGW hits the stores! kkplzthx!'<br>
Cheers. <p>Halo 57th Beguiler<br>
